        <Parent_String>metallophones [300195385], percussion plaques [300195373], percussion idiophones: solid-bodied [300209184], percussion idiophones [300195371], directly struck idiophones [300041659], struck idiophones [300041657], idiophones [300041646], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metallophones consisting of tuned, graduated metal bars arranged in two rows suspended from a metal frame with tubular resonators suspended below them; motor-driven spinning discs fixed above the open tops of the resonators produce the unique vibrato characteristic of the instrument.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slaginstrumenten, met gestemde, metalen toetsen, in 2 rijen opgehangen in een raamwerk, met pijpen eronder in de open bovenkanten waarvan schijfjes, door een motortje draaiend gehouden, voor vibrato zorgen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由有度定音高並循序排列獨金屬條所組成的鐵琴，金屬條以雙排排列，懸掛於金屬框上，管狀共鳴器則吊於其下，固定於共鳴器的開放式頂部上方，以引擎驅動急速旋轉的圓盤，可製造出作為這個樂器特色的獨特顫音。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metallofon aus gestimmten, abgestuften Metallplatten, die in zwei Reihen auf einem Metallrahmen angeordnet sind, unter denen Röhrenresonatoren hängen; von einem Elektromotor angetriebene Drehscheiben, die oberhalb der offenen Enden der Resonatoren angebracht sind, erzeugen das einzigartige Vibrato, das für das Instrument charakteristisch ist.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metalofones constituídos por barras metálicas graduadas afinadas dispostas em duas filas suspensas de uma armação metálica com ressoadores tubulares suspensos abaixo delas; discos giratórios acionados por motor fixados acima dos topos abertos dos ressonadores produzem a característica única de vibrato do instrumento.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
